To convert the volume from \pu{cm^{3}} to \pu{\A^{3}}, we use the conversion factor: 1 \pu{\A} = 10^{-8} cm. Therefore, 1 cm^{3} = (10^{8})^{3} \pu{\A^{3}} = 10^{24} \pu{\A^{3}}. Now, we can convert the volume of a single gold atom: 1.252 x 10^{-23} cm^{3} * 10^{24} \pu{\A^{3}}/cm^{3} = 12.52 \pu{\A^{3}}.

